Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of social media as a tool for creating networked publics and mobilizing collective action, which falls under the category of social computing (cs.SI). It also touches on the use of data from citizens as sensors, which could fall under the categories of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) and sensor networks (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the potential impact on society, which could fall under the categories of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
